SENATE RESOLUTION 292
By McNally
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Cathy Kolb of
Clarksville to the State Board of Education.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-301, provides for the creation of
the State Board of Education; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-301, further provides that the
Speaker of the Senate shall appoint members representing the third, fourth, and seventh
congressional districts to the State Board of Education; and
WHEREAS, Speaker Randy McNally has appointed Cathy Kolb of Clarksville to the
State Board of Education as a member representing the Seventh Congressional District for a
term that will expire on March 31, 2029; and
WHEREAS, a highly respected member of her community, Cathy Kolb is an educator
with more than thirty years of experience and currently serves as a special education teacher at
Moore Magnet STEM Elementary School for the Clarksville-Montgomery County School
System; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Kolb holds a Bachelor of Science degree from Western Kentucky
University and Master of Arts and Education Specialist degrees from Austin Peay State
University; and
WHEREAS, Cathy Kolb is a person of integrity and an active citizen whose
benevolence, acumen, and strong commitment to public service have helped to enhance the
well-being of this State and its citizens; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-301, provides that each member
appointed by the Speaker of the Senate to the State Board of Education shall be subject to
confirmation by the Senate; now, therefore,
SR0292
012837
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that this body does hereby confirm
the appointment of Cathy Kolb of Clarksville to the State Board of Education as a member
representing the Seventh Congressional District for a term that will expire on March 31, 2029.
